apable of executing multi-step tasks including:\n   - Writing code\n   - Debugging and running applications\n   - Writing tests\n   - Verifying results\n\n3. **Performance Benchmarks**: Junie achieved **53.6% task completion** on the SWE-Bench Verified benchmark test, showing above-average performance.\n\n4. **Supported IDEs**:\n   - IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate\n   - PyCharm Professional\n   - WebStorm\n   - GoLand\n   - Coming soon: PhpStorm, RustRover, and RubyMine\n\n### Key Features:\n- **Complementary to AI Assistant**: While AI Assistant focuses on code suggestions, Junie specializes in complex multi-step tasks\n- **Multi-model Support**: Upgraded AI Assistant now supports Anthropic Claude 3.7 Sonnet and Google Gemini 2.5 Pro\n- **Flexible Model Selection**: Developers can switch between JetBrains' Junie, Anthropic's Claude, or Google's Gemini within the IDE\n\n### Pricing (2026):\n- **AI Free**: Included with all IDE licenses (unlimited code completion + local AI)\n- **AI Pro**: $10/month\n- **AI Ultimate**: $20/month\n- All Products Pack includes AI Pro\n\nThe search results indicate that rather than a specific February 2026 release, JetBrains has been **incrementally rolling out and expanding access** to Junie throughout 2025, with the February 2026 announcement focusing more on the new free tier availability rather than a new product release.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
